title candidate_assessments.Status — CandidateAssessment lifecycle (plain string column, no enum)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<terminal>> #FFECEC
}

[*] --> Queued : CandidateAssessmentService.TriggerAssessmentAsync\nnew CandidateAssessment { Status = "Queued" }\nenqueued on ICandidateAssessmentQueue

state Queued
state Running
state Completed <<terminal>>
state Failed <<terminal>>
state Cancelled <<terminal>>

Queued --> Running : BackgroundCandidateAssessmentProcessor picks the job\nProcessAssessmentJobAsync -> Status = "Running"\n(AI service Line 2: 16-task validated DAG)
Running --> Completed : DAG sink task L2-015 done\nStatus = "Completed"; CompletedAtUtc set
Running --> Failed : exception during processing\nStatus = "Failed"; FailedStage + FailureReason populated
Running --> Cancelled : OperationCanceledException inside\nProcessAssessmentJobAsync (:860 / :891 on the re-fetched row)
Queued --> Cancelled : CandidateAssessmentService.CancelAssessmentAsync (:1710)
Running --> Cancelled : CandidateAssessmentService.CancelAssessmentAsync (:1710)

Failed --> Queued : BackgroundCandidateAssessmentBackfillProcessor (:128)\nre-queues eligible assessments
Cancelled --> Queued : BackgroundCandidateAssessmentBackfillProcessor (:128)

Completed --> [*]
Failed --> [*]
Cancelled --> [*]

note as N_STALE #FFF0F0
  <b>Stale-comment discrepancy</b>
  CandidateAssessment.cs:24 comments the column as
    // Queued, Running, Completed, Failed
  — four values. The service also writes <b>"Cancelled"</b> in three
  places (CandidateAssessmentService.cs:860, :891, :1710), so the real
  value set is five. The comment has not been updated.
end note

note right of Running
  Progress is streamed to the client over SSE
  (GET api/v1/candidate-assessments/progress/{userId})
  via PublishProgressAsync / PublishRawProgressAsync, and
  cancellation is additionally signalled to the AI service
  through the Redis key ai:cancel:{correlation_id}.
end note

note right of Cancelled
  Cancellation is written twice on the failure path: once on the
  tracked `assessment` instance (:860) and once on a freshly
  re-fetched row (:891), because the tracked entity may be stale
  after the cancellation token fired mid-pipeline.
end note

note as N_QUEUE
  ⚠ ICandidateAssessmentQueue is a singleton IN-PROCESS queue and is
  NOT durable (GROUND-TRUTH §5.4). Unlike repository analysis jobs,
  there is no dedicated startup sweeper for candidate assessments —
  a process restart leaves rows stranded in Queued or Running until
  the backfill processor picks them up.
end note

@enduml
